        <h2 class="">Why Enroll Your Child in Saddle Mountain USD #90?</h2>
        <ul class="">
<li class="">Saddle Mountain students demonstrate the <a href="https://azednews.com/saddle-mountain-among-top-districts-nation-academic-gains/" title="" alt="" target="_blank">highest levels of educational gains in Arizona and one of the highest in the country</a>!</li>
<li class="">Tonopah Valley High School ranked among nation's best in 2016 by <a href="http://www.usnews.com/education/best-high-schools/arizona/districts/saddle-mountain-unified-school-district/tonopah-valley-high-school-1073" title="" alt="" target="_blank">US News &amp; World Report</a>.</li>
            <li class="">137 of 137 (100%) of TVHS seniors graduated in 2019!</li>
<li class="">80% of seniors are planning to continue their education</li>
<li class="">Seniors earned $3.8 million in scholarships in 2019!</li>
            <li class="">Free all-day kindergarten</li>
            <li class="">A computer for every student</li>
            <li class="">Four-day school week schedule</li>
            <li class="">Award-winning teachers and principals</li>
            <li class="">Highly-qualified, appropriately-certified teachers</li>
            <li class="">Advanced math for 7th and 8th graders</li>
            <li class="">AP and dual-enrollment courses</li>
            <li class="">Career/Technical education classes</li>
            <li class="">Wide choice of activities and sports</li>
            <li class="">Family atmosphere</li>
            <li class="">Silver LEED-certified elementary school</li>
            <li class="">Upgraded modern facilities</li>
            <li class="">Free breakfast for all students</li>
            <li class="">High school students earned over 450 hours of college credit over the past two years.</li>
<li class="">Saddle Mountain USD is the metro area leader and a top district in the nation in how much students learn each year according to <a href="https://edopportunity.org/explorer/#/map/us/districts/grd/ses/all/9.5/33.46/-111.97" title="" alt="" target="_blank">a new visualization tool from Stanford University!</a>
</li>
            
            
            
        </ul>
<h2 class="">Mission Statement</h2>
        <p class="">Educate all students to become responsible, college-and-career-ready community members.</p>

        <h2 class="">Goals</h2>
        <ol>
<li class="">
<strong>Educational Programs &amp; Services:</strong> SMUSD will provide a superior education geared toward student success by maintaining, developing, and implementing high quality programs and services.</li>
            <li class="">
<strong>Students:</strong> SMUSD will prepare all students to graduate college and career ready. </li>
            <li class="">
<strong>Staff:</strong> SMUSD will attract, develop, and retain high quality, dedicated staff who believe all children are capable of success.</li>
            <li class="">
<strong>Community:</strong> SMUSD will achieve its mission and vision by engaging all stakeholders.</li>
            <li class="">
<b>Asset Management: </b>SMUSD will effectively manage facilities, finances, and resources in support of student learning.<b></b>
</li>
        </ol>
